.TH "snd_hda_get_conn_list" 9 "snd_hda_get_conn_list" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_get_conn_list \- get connection list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hda_get_conn_list
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "const hda_nid_t **listp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HDA codec
.IP "nid" 12
NID to parse
.IP "listp" 12
the pointer to store NID list
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Parses the connection list of the given widget and stores the pointer
to the list of NIDs.

Returns the number of connections, or a negative error code.

Note that the returned pointer isn't protected against the list
modification.  If \fBsnd_hda_override_conn_list\fP might be called
concurrently, protect with a mutex appropriately.
